-- Gazprom Interested in Bidding for BP Russian, Caspian Assets, Times Says
-- Kristen Schweizer
-- 2010-07-03T10:43:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-03/gazprom-interested-in-bidding-for-bp-russian-caspian-assets-times-says.html

          
          
             G azprom OAO  is looking at assets in
Russia and the Caspian region held by  BP Plc  as the U.K. oil
company moves ahead with a $10 billion sale of international
businesses, the London-based Times said, citing unidentified
persons.  
 The holdings include BP’s 25.5 percent stake in the Shah
Deniz project in Azerbaijan, the Times said, adding that no
formal talks have been held. French oil company Total SA has
also expressed interest in BP’s assets, the newspaper said.  
